title: Philippines up to One Day Interbank Rate
description: Philippines up to One Day Interbank Rate was at 4.22 percent on Monday November 7. Interbank Rate in Philippines averaged 7.74 percent from 1990 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 102.63 percent in October of 1997 and a record low of 0 percent in March of 2017. In Philippines, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - Philippines up to One Day Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bangko Sentral Ng Pilipinas
